The Qt Design Studio 3.4.0 release contains bug fixes and new features.

The most important changes are listed in this document.
For more complete lists of changes, see release reports for Qt Design Studio
3.4.0: https://bugreports.qt.io/projects/QDS/versions/20141

General
  * Added missing crashpad in macOS installation (QDS-5958)
  * Added download of data for tutorials and examples from qt.io (QDS-6886)
  * Added context menu for setting ui.qml and main.qml file in project editor (QDS-6882)
  * Fixed hanging application when adding a new file not in the project path (QDS-6870)
  * Fixed hanging application closing project while editing component (QDS-6841)
  * Fixed the 2d preview of the form editor in a pure 3d scene (QDS-6896)
  * Updated focus behavior of controls in property editor (QDS-6028)

Curve Editor
  * Fixed state related bug in curve editor (QDS-6872)
  * Fixed invalid animation ranges (QDS-6543)
  * Fixed toolbar (QDS-6542)
  * Added informative text if document has no timeline (QDS-6545)

Examples
  * Added Robot Arm example (QDS-6899)
  * Added simple Qt Quick 3D example (QDS-6716)
  * Added Figma Variant example (QDS-6833)
  * Updated particle effect example (QDS-6712)

Documentation
  * Added Android live preview to public documentation (QDS-5729)

Qt Bridge for Figma
  * Fixed asset export error crash handling (QDS-6916)
  * Fixed warnings for variant state name duplicates (QDS-6819)
  * Added anchors support (QDS-6890)

